LEGENDARY Nigerian musician, Alex Okoroigwe aka Alex O is making a great comeback with a German-based Nigerian star, Prince Amaho. According to information at The Nation’s disposal, Amaho will be working with Alex O on a new song and video from Alex’s comeback projects. The singer will also be setting up his German-based Powersonic Music record label in a collaboration project with Alex O in Nigeria. PowerSonic Music Nigeria will be signing on and supporting rising artists in the country. Already, Prince Amaho and Alex O are excited about the musical collaboration project, as it is expected to open doors to many other projects and platforms that will help to further propel more Nigerian music acts to the global stage.   I look forward to young talents telling stories with dance –…     Tiwa Savage, others Bag Women4Africa award     Hollywood actress Tasha Smith spoils Jemeji star with over…   These projects are to precede a musical tour of Nigeria and Africa, featuring Prince Amaho himself, the Soul Bros, Alex O, Baron D, and other Nigerian artists. Alex O is a popular Nigerian chart-topping, awards-winning musician of the 90s, who made major hit songs like Celebrate, Do It, Nwadamma, and Banana among others. On his part, Amaho, who was born into the Ike Royal family in Owerri, Imo State, got a major break with his first single release, Rhythm in My Life under the BMG music label after relocating to Germany in the 90s. In 2009, Amaho came up with a musical project called Soul Bros. Alongside the group, he has gone on to make major club hits and Chart-topping entries worldwide, touring every city in Europe, with both original songs and covers of top hits like All Night Long, Gimme Hope Joanna, Bad Boys to mention but a few. His original hit songs like, Wake Up, Cry Out, Freedom, Celebrate, etc, are still trending worldwide.